@database DirlistClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - Dirlist Class"


Dirlist class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "ListClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The Dirlist class is used to create a list of the entries of a
  directory.

  Dirlist can only be used with Listviews.

  See @{"List" LINK "ListClass.guide/Main"} @{"Listview" LINK "ListviewFunctions.guide/Main"}.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}AcceptPattern@{fg text}
  S IS
  An AmigaDOS pattern

  @{fg shine}AutoReRead@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  If you change the value of some attributes, e.g. AcceptPatten,
  RejectPatten or DrawersOnly, you would need to invoke a ReRead
  on the object to make the changes active. This attribute forces
  the object to re-read its directory at any change. Default 1.

  @{fg shine}Directory@{fg text}
  S ISGN

  @{fg shine}DrawersOnly@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}FilesOnly@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}FilterDrawers@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}NumBytes@{fg text}
  N G

    @{fg shine}NumDrawers@{fg text}
  N G

  @{fg shine}NumFiles@{fg text}
  N G

  @{fg shine}Path@{fg text}
  S G

  @{fg shine}RejectIcons@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}RejectPattern@{fg text}
  S IS
  An AmigaDOS pattern

  @{fg shine}ShowTitle@{fg text}
  B I
  Set to 1 to sow the list title

  @{fg shine}SortDirs@{fg text}
  M G2N
  ISGN A number or one of:
     o First
     o Last
     o Mix

  @{fg shine}SortHighLow@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}SortType@{fg text}
  M G2N
  ISGN A number or one of:
     o Date
     o Name
     o Size

  @{fg shine}Status@{fg text}
  N GN
  The status of the object, one of:
     o 0 - Invalid
     o 1 - Reading
     o 2 - OK

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}GetEntry@{fg text}
  <pos>,<stem/V> Get an entry.
  pos is a number or Active
  The field of stem set are:
     o Name
     o EntryType: <0 file, >0 dir


  @{fg shine}ReRead@{fg text}
  -
  Re-read the directory

@EndNode
